SIMPLE: secularist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Secularist
<hw>Sec"u*lar*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who theoretically rejects
every form of religious faith, and every kind of religious worship, and
accepts only the facts and influences which are derived from the present
life; also, one who believes that education and other matters of civil
policy should be managed without the introduction of a religious
element.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secularity</ent>⟦br⟧
